cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is about unsupervised domain adaptation in person re-identification, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel adaptation framework that involves memory and invariance learning, which are topics that are often studied in machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its approach on large-scale benchmarks, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR) research.
